      "acceptanceCriteria": "Verified FEA software with documented quality management system and version control meeting or exceeding required gradation for medium model risk.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2 used under ISO 9001-certified QMS; FDA in-house solver independently verified; software validation records on file for all three ensemble members."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification against analytical solutions or Method of Manufactured Solutions for relevant element types and boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Patch tests and cantilever beam benchmarks completed for all solid and contact element types used; results within 0.5% of analytical solutions across all three codes."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating quantity-of-interest change less than 5% between successive refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed; peak von Mises stress at screw-rod interface converged to within 2.1% between medium and fine meshes; final mesh selected at medium refinement for computational efficiency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance verified within 1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals monitored across all 50 load increments; maximum residual 4.3e-7; energy balance error 0.3%; direct sparse solver used to eliminate iterative convergence concerns."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented modeling protocol with independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in original construction.",
      "rationale": "Modeling protocol document v2.3 reviewed by independent senior analyst; boundary condition application and material property assignment independently verified; no use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection justified by literature and sensitivity analysis; contact formulation and material constitutive model appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending of titanium alloy constructs.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) constitutive model justified by stress levels remaining below yield in rod; augmented Lagrangian contact at screw-rod interface validated against frictionless and frictional variants; model form uncertainty estimated at 4.2% via sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs derived from traceable measurements with uncertainty quantification; sensitivity of QoI to input variability documented.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus 114 GPa per ASTM E8 coupon tests (n=6, CV=1.2%); screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements of production hardware; one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis shows QoI sensitivity to modulus less than 1.5% across ±3σ range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Production-representative hardware from same manufacturing lot used for both experimental and computational model inputs; sample size sufficient to characterize construct-to-construct variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs from single production lot; CMM measurements confirm dimensional conformance within drawing tolerances; inter-construct stiffness CV=3.8% demonstrating acceptable manufacturing consistency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of loading rates and environmental conditions; at minimum two independent test conditions evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Only single ASTM F1717 standard test condition evaluated (5 mm/min crosshead displacement, ambient temperature, dry); clinical loading rate variation and in vivo thermal environment not explored. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this shortfall is acknowledged and accepted by the credibility assessment team given the prescriptive nature of the regulatory submission context."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading demonstrably equivalent to experimental setup; fixture compliance characterized and incorporated.",
      "rationale": "Test fixture compliance measured (0.12 mm/kN) and incorporated as spring elements in FEA; loading platen alignment verified by strain gauge rosettes on reference specimens; boundary condition equivalency confirmed within 1.8% of applied moment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric or equivalent) applied; prediction within experimental uncertainty band for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness predictions from all three ensemble members fall within ±1 experimental standard deviation for 10 of 11 specimens; ensemble mean error 2.7%; ASME V&V 20 validation metric U_val=0.94 exceeding threshold of 0.85."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly linked to device safety and performance claim; construct stiffness and peak interface stress relevant to fatigue life prediction for non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness under compression-bending is the primary regulatory submission QoI per FDA guidance; peak screw-rod interface stress is secondary QoI informing fatigue margin; both quantities directly support the device safety claim for Class II spinal fixation hardware."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions sufficiently similar to intended use scenario to support extrapolation of credibility evidence.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on production 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws under ASTM F1717 compression-bending — directly matching the regulatory submission test configuration; two-laboratory replication confirms result generalizability; extrapolation to clinical loading requires acknowledgment of single test condition shortfall documented under Test conditions factor."
    }
  ],
